        <abstract>
            <p>Regarding CD’s inability to find a young botanist to investigate Russian wheat; comments on utter lack of organisation in scientific research in Britain as compared with Germany.</p> 
<p>Gives arguments against CD’s suggestion that the <hi rend="italic">saxonka</hi> seeds could have long dormancy period which would account for their gradual overtaking of <hi rend="italic">kubanka</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
